cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for facial expression recognition and affective computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses deep neural networks and evaluation metrics, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves querying search engines and collecting data from the internet, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
